Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Drain and rinse @chickpeas{1%400g can}; pat dry with #paper towels{}. Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into ½-inch pieces (halve lengthwise first if carrots are on the larger side).

Toss chickpeas on one side of a #baking sheet{} with half the @veggie stock concentrate{2}, half the @shawarma spice blend{1%tablespoon}, a drizzle of @cooking oil{4%teaspoon}, @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss carrots on empty side of sheet with remaining Shawarma Spice Blend, another drizzle of oil, salt, and pepper.

Roast on top rack until chickpeas are browned and crispy and carrots are browned and tender, ~{18-22%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, half the @chili powder{1%teaspoon} (you'll use more later), remaining stock concentrate, @water{1 1/4%cups}, and a pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, then reduce to simmer; cover and cook until tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, finely chop @parsley{1/4%ounce}. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}. Mince @jalapeño{1}, removing ribs and seeds for less heat. Roughly chop @pistachios{1/2%ounce}.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with paper towels and season all over with salt and pepper. Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken (skin sides down); cook chicken until cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Transfer to a #cutting board{}.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #medium pan{} over high heat. Add @grape tomatoes{4%ounce}; cook, stirring occasionally, until blistered, ~{2-3%minutes}. Remove pan from heat; season with salt and pepper.

== Schug Sauce ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine parsley, half the @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, remaining chili powder, @olive oil{1 1/2%tablespoon}, a big squeeze of lemon juice, and as much jalapeño as you like. Season with salt and pepper.

== Lemon Aioli ==

In a separate small bowl, combine @vegan mayo{4%tablespoon}, remaining garlic powder, @sugar{1/4%teaspoon}, a squeeze of lemon juice, and a pinch of lemon zest. Add @water{1%tsp} 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with salt and pepper.

== Assembly ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in a drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} and season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice between #bowls{}; top with chickpeas, carrots, and tomatoes. Drizzle everything with lemon aioli and schug sauce. Garnish with pistachios and serve with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.

Slice chicken crosswise (skip slicing salmon); serve chicken atop bowls.